        public TabSwitcherStyle(@NonNull
                        TabSwitcher tabSwitcher,
                        @NonNull
                        Model model,
                        @NonNull
                        ThemeHelper themeHelper)
        Creates a new class, which allows to retrieve the style attributes of a TabSwitcher.
        Parameters:
        tabSwitcher - The tab switcher, whose style attributes are retrieved, as an instance of the type TabSwitcher. The tab switcher may not be null
        model - The model of the tab switcher, whose style attributes are retrieved, as an instance of the class TabSwitcher. The model may not be null
        themeHelper - The theme helper, which allows to retrieve resources, depending on the tab switcher's theme, as an instance of the class ThemeHelper. The theme helper may not be null

      • getAddTabButtonColor

        public final android.content.res.ColorStateList getAddTabButtonColor()
        Returns the color of the button, which allows to add a new tab. When using the smartphone layout, such a button is never shown. When using the tablet layout, the button is shown next to the tabs.
        Returns:
        The color of the button, which allows to add a new tab, as an instance of the class ColorStateList or null, if the default color is used

      • getToolbarTitle
